reviews.text:
Went on a Sunday around noon. Not too busy. Great service, very attentive, food was pretty good and a good amount of food. Had great options of non-gluten food for my friend.

Pros:
-Good Service
-Fast Service
-Food was fast
-Good Drinks
-Food was good (Not Amazing)

Cons: Seating was close to other people (Not a big problem)

I had the Margherita pizza which was good, but a little wet from a puddle of grease in the middle. Overall all the food was good.

I had a great experience dining at Bohemian Brewery! I tried the Garlic Burger, Egg Florentine, and French Toast ‚Äî and everything was delicious. The bun on the Garlic Burger was fresh and flavorful, and the sauce on the Egg Florentine was so tasty and well-balanced. The French Toast was absolutely awesome ‚Äî perfectly cooked with just the right amount of sweetness.

The service was excellent. The staff were all very friendly, welcoming, and attentive, which made the experience even better.

The interior design is very interesting and cozy. I especially loved the fireplace ‚Äî it adds a warm and charming touch to the atmosphere. It‚Äôs a great spot whether you‚Äôre grabbing brunch or enjoying a casual meal with friends or family.

Parking is easy and convenient, and it‚Äôs nice that they also offer a kid‚Äôs menu, making it a family-friendly place.

Definitely worth checking out if you‚Äôre in the area. I‚Äôll be coming back to try more!

Fred is the coolest guy! He was the friendliest and so funny. Service was phenomenal.

Apparently they haven't changed their main menu in 20+ years so you can count on getting your favorite dishes every time you visit.

The ambience is so cozy. I love the feeling of being in a big cabin with a fireplace.

The fries are on par with Bruge's though they don't have such amazing dipping sauces. We like the salmon fish and chips, pierogies, brats, and chicken schnitzel. We got a great blackened chicken sandwich yesterday that was a daily special. Delicious!

The pretzel and beer cheese is totally worth the $12 dollars.

The food is pricey but worth splurging for on occasion.

And they will give you a free dumpling dessert on your birthday without singing to you!

Bohemian Brewery totally blew us away. The vibe of the place made us feel like we were in a cozy pub somewhere in Germany‚Äîsuper authentic, warm, and inviting. Great atmosphere for both beer lovers and casual diners.

We tried a few of their beers and really enjoyed them, but the standout for me was definitely the Viennese Lager‚Äîsmooth, flavorful, and just the right balance. You can tell they take their brewing seriously here.

For food, we ordered the Brewmaster‚Äôs Basket, which came with fried calamari and fries‚Äîcrispy, tasty, and perfect for sharing. We also got the chicken wings, and they were delicious‚Äîgreat flavor, cooked just right.

The service was excellent‚Äîfriendly, fast, and the staff knew their beers well, which is always a plus when you‚Äôre exploring different styles.

Overall, Bohemian Brewery was a great experience from start to finish. Amazing beer, great food, and awesome vibes. Definitely coming back!

Fantastic!
Enormous portions!
Everything we tried was awesome.
We started with the giant pub pretzel w/ beer cheese and the pirogies.
We had the beef stroganoff, pork shank, garlic burgers and a flatbread. All were amazing!
We will definitely return when we are in town again.

editorial_summary.overview: Eclectic microbrewery crafting traditional lagers & European-inspired pub grub in lodgelike digs.
